es poverty, hunger, homelessness and access to health care for the under-served. Hes also currently pursuing a degree in Business Administration. He and his wife Marissa have four dogs.'),(4572,485,'_bio','field_5c18481dad668'),(4574,486,'photo','467'),(4575,486,'_photo','field_5c18482cad669'),(4576,486,'position','Senior Account Executive'),(4577,486,'_position','field_5c1847a7ad664'),(4578,486,'group','Waste Division'),(4579,486,'_group','field_5c1847d4ad665'),(4580,486,'phone','828-651-8550'),(4581,486,'_phone','field_5c1847fbad666'),(4582,486,'phone_extension','yes'),(4583,486,'_phone_extension','field_5c185050fa7ae'),(4584,486,'extension','1120'),(4585,486,'_extension','field_5c184ffdfa7ad'),(4586,486,'email','paul.nelson@emoffitt.com'),(4587,486,'_email','field_5c184812ad667'),(4588,486,'bio','Paul started his career at Moffitt International in the summer of 2004 and has built a national network of clients in the Waste and Recycling industry. Prior to joining Moffitt, Paul worked in the hospitality and restaurant industries.\r\n\r\nPaul is involved with a number of charitable causes, including Manna Food Bank and Project Healing Waters, an organization that works with disabled veterans using fly-fishing as a means of therapy. As both a veteran and a fly fisherman himself, Paul is extremely proud of the work they do.\r\n\r\nPaul was born in Michigan and relocated with his family to Florida when he was young. After high school, he joined the military. Paul and his wife of over 30 years still live in the same house that they raised their children in. They have one granddaughter. '),(4589,486,'_bio','field_5c18481dad668'),(4591,487,'photo','476'),(4592,487,'_photo','field_5c18482cad669'),(4593,487,'position','Account Executive'),(4594,487,'_position','field_5c1847a7ad664'),(4595,487,'group','Construction NY'),(4596,487,'_group','field_5c1847d4ad665'),(4597,487,'phone','828-651-8550'),(4598,487,'_phone','field_5c1847fbad666'),(4599,487,'phone_extension','yes'),(460