wsuits from suits, and potential fines. Not to mention the number one cost item in your winter heating budget: fuel and more fuel. Did I mention fuel?\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nBy taking advantage of newer and more efficient technology, contractors can save thousandseven millionsof dollars in fuel expenses, and run a safer, more productive shop.\r\n\r\nPatrick Heintz from<a href=\"https://www.aggreko.com/en-us\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">Aggreko</a>has some tips on the latest heating technologies for construction sites in Construction Executive magazine:\r\n\r\n<b>Heating Tips to Keep Construction Jobs Running in Winter</b>\r\n\r\nBy Patrick Heintz | Construction Executive | January 11, 2019\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://constructionexec.com/article/heating-tips-to-keep-construction-jobs-running-in-winter\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">http://constructionexec.com/article/heating-tips-to-keep-construction-jobs-running-in-winter</a>\r\n\r\n<i>A strong temporary heating package from an experienced provider is critical to maintaining construction through the winter, but there is more at stake with a winter heating program.</i>','Heating Tips for Construction','','publish','closed','closed','','heating-tips-for-construction','','','2019-02-01 17:17:52','2019-02-01 17:17:52','',0,'http://absdsgn.com/dev/moffitt/?p=596',0,'post','',0),(597,1,'2019-02-01 17:15:41','2019-02-01 17:15:41','How do you warm your crew and their equipment in the winter months? Keeping your construction site warm on cold winter days can be essential to completing a project on time. And avoiding unnecessary site shutdowns is a real cost saver.\r\n\r\nThrowing down a few smoggy<a href=\"https://everipedia.org/wiki/lang_en/Salamander_heater/\" data-blogger-escaped-target=\"_blank\">salamanders</a>in work areas can risk a call from the health and safety police. A dangerous heating system runs the risk of causing fires, fuel spills, lawsuits from suits, and potential fines. Not to mention th